  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Build a school for 100 Maasai children in Tanzania</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Children in Kiruru village have to walk 10 miles every day to attend the nearest primary school. They are regularly attacked by wild animals and last year 3 were washed away in the Terat river. The village has been trying to build their own school for the past 2 years. This project will help them finish it, and build accommodation for the teachers. Parents will be more willing to let kids go to school if it is near, so more of Kiruru&apos;s children will be able to go to school, and remain safe.</narrative>
  </description>
